-- Russia’s RTS Index Extends Decline, Drops 21% From 2012 Peak
-- B y   K s e n i a   G a l o u c h k o
-- 2012-05-14T14:31:44Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-05-14/russia-s-rts-index-extends-decline-drops-21-from-2012-peak.html
Russia’s dollar-denominated RTS Index
extended declines, taking its drop from this year’s peak to more
than 20 percent.  The gauge traded down 3.6 percent at 1,401.03 as of 6:26
p.m. in Moscow, a 21 percent slide from its 2012 intraday high
reached on March 19.  To contact the reporter on this story:
